'''''El Wa3ra''''', sometimes written '''''El Waara''''' ({{lang-ar|الواعرة}}, translated as ''The Tricked'') is an Algerian [[hidden camera]] [[Pranks|pranking]] [[television series]], created and produced by Rym Ghazali, and starring Ghazali herself alongside Chemseddine Lamrani. It airs everyday during [[Ramadan]], starting May 27, 2017, on [[Echorouk TV]].<ref name="algpress.com">[http://www.algpress.com/article-187388.htm These journalists are victims of the "hidden camera" in Ramadan 2017!](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="babalweb">[http://www.babalweb.net/ar/info/242006-%D9%87%D8%A4%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%B6%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%B6%D8%A7%D9%86-2017-!.html These are the victims of "El Wa3ra" in Ramadan 2017!](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref>

== Background ==
The series is presented by Algerian singer, actress, TV presenter and producer Rym Ghazali, alongside the YouTuber Chemseddine Lamrani, better known as DZjoker.

The idea of the program is to invite guests to different locations, and record them on [[hidden camera]] while they get in a frightening situation. The show mixes the actual images with scenes in which the participant views the hidden camera footage and comments on it.<ref name="algpress.com" /><ref name="elhiwardz.com">[http://elhiwardz.com/?p=85564 Artists News – El Wa3ra Program.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="aljazair24.com">[http://aljazair24.com/featured/42674.html A variety of programs on Echorouk TV.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="oran-news-24.com">[http://www.oran-news-24.com/index.php/2017/05/20/ramadhan-2017-echourouk-tv-et-el-djazairia-mettent-le-paquet/ Ramadhan 2017 Echourouk TV and El Djazairia One put the package.](in French). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="arabstoday.net.200">[http://www.arabstoday.net/200/200427-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B5%D8%AF%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B6%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%81-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%82%D9%82-%D8%A3%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%A6%D8%B1 "El Wa3ra" shocks guests and achieves the highest viewing rate in Algeria.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref>

According to Media & Market Research (MMR) agency, ''El Wa3ra'' is the most watched program during the 2017 Ramadan season.<ref>[http://heloualfan.com/2017/06/04/%D8%AD%D9%84%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A9-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%BA%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B0-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89/ The artist Rym Ghazali holds the highest views in her comedy program.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.sehranin.com/?p=1218 Rym Ghazali holds the highest views.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.panet.co.il/article/1787825 Artist Rym Ghazali achieved the forefront in her comic program 'El Wa3ra'.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://beirutnewscenter.com/single_page.php?id=45310&head=%C3%CE%C8%C7%D1%20%DD%E4%ED%C9&cat=26  Rym Ghazali achieved the lead in 'El Wa3ra'.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://alwanegypt.com/2017/06/05/%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AC-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%AE%D8%B1%D8%AC-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%88%D9%81-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%82%D9%82/ "El Wa3ra" program is out of the ordinary and achieves the highest viewing rate in Algeria.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[https://aljaras.com/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%BA%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B0-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A3%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%81%D9%8A/Rym Ghazali captures the highest views at (El Wa3ra) – Aljaras.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://assadamagazine.com/2017/06/04/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A9-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%BA%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B0-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87/ Rym Ghazali Acquires the highest viewing of her comic program .. El Wa3ra.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.annachraalikhbaria.com/2017/06/blog-post_68.html El Wa3ra ... Rym Ghazali achieves the highest levels of viewing in Ramadan.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.albiladpress.com/news/2017/3156/spaces/431171.html Rym Ghazali captures the highest views in her comedy program.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref> It is also considered by people and some media as "the best comic program" broadcast on Echorouk TV in Ramadan 2017, in terms of content.<ref name="alwatanvoice">[https://www.alwatanvoice.com/arabic/news/2017/06/04/1056845.html Rym Ghazali holds the highest views.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="elfagr">[http://www.elfagr.org/2619640 "El Wa3ra" program dumps of the Algerian Rym Ghazali grabs attention.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref name="syriaalyom.com">[https://syriaalyom.com/index/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%BA%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B0-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A3%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%81%D9%8A/ Rym Ghazali holds the highest views.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 7, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.khabar3ajel.com/media/tv%E2%80%8E/ El Wa3ra The most powerful programs on Echorouk TV.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref>

The series is also viewed in Tunisia and Morocco, and by [[Maghrebis]] who are living in France.<ref name="alwatanvoice.com">[https://www.alwatanvoice.com/arabic/news/2017/06/09/1058379.html "El Wa3ra "crossing the borders of Algeria to Morocco, Tunisia and France with a significant follow-up rate.](in Arabic). Retrieved June 9, 2017.</ref> This success comes, according to ''Al Watan Voice'', from the creativity in the various scenes filmed in Algeria, especially in the [[Algerian Desert]], in addition to the participation of leading Algerian media and drama figures.<ref name="alwatanvoice.com" />

